President Obama called President Karzai to congratulate him and his wife on the birth of their daughter. They discussed their shared commitment to the Lisbon framework, which aims to have Afghan forces take full responsibility for security by the end of 2014. They also talked about building capable Afghan security forces and strengthening Afghan sovereignty. The leaders discussed President Karzai's concerns about night raids and house searches, and agreed to continue negotiations on a Memorandum of Understanding. They also talked about President Karzai's concerns about foreign troops in Afghan villages. President Obama invited President Karzai to the NATO Summit in May to discuss the next phase of transition. They agreed to stay in close touch.